A Durban pensioner died in a house fire in the Westville area, paramedic services said on Monday. Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said the victim was 70 years old. "He passed away due to severe burns from the fire." It is unclear how the fire started. Jamieson said police and fire services were investigating the incident. https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/durban-pensioner-dies-in-house-fire-20180507